ple leaving to join raiding or uber guilds.<br>I personally have only ever been in small giulds and this is great until about level 45.  After that level I have found small giulds pretty frustrating - not because of not getting Uber gear but the fact that it is difficult or near impossible for a smaller giuld to go to the harder zones.  I have pretty much had a policy of not raiding with other giulds as I felt I should be avail for guild stuff - which has meant I have never been on a Hate Raid only been too Fear twice and never been to most of the top level zones.<br>SM is capable of many things but <br>(1) we need too be dedicated to making raids work <br><br>(2)people have to be willing to take a risk in their gameplay<br><br>(3) we have to be more open in our gameplay - ie : if we dont have a certain class for a raid try to work out alternatives too game play rather then call off a raid.<br><br>(4) when raiding ensuring that we have an objective - wether it be fun or items and achieve it<br><br>(5)make sure raids have a purpose that is reasonable to everyone involved - ie: not raiding for epic items for low level members when a higher level person may require assistance that will complete a quest or item which will be of overall benefit to their character and therefore the guild.<br><br>(6)spontaneous raiding - why is so difficult to organise a quick raid when half the guild is on<br><br>(7)the guild cannot expect to retain high level characters or attract them to join if there are no opportunities or challenges<br>for people of that level<br><br>(<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> we need more members not guild twinks <br><br>If anyone takes offence at anything I have written you were not meant too - its not personally directed at anyone.<br>Anyway just thought I should express the above and explain the reasons why, if I left, I would be joining an Uber guild - not for the items as such but to be able to explore, fight in most of the top end areas that I have never been too and yes too at least have a chance some of the top end items.<br>One other thing for a high level in top end zones unless you get uber loot your character becomes unplayable- you just dont have the stats - so maybe that should be considered too as a reason why people leave.<br>anyway thats my rant<br>Masten Blasten Mage<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ustrydr69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>strydr69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/02 4:29:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just a thought or two</span><hr size=1> actually masten...your points sound 100% right...<br><br>i vote for you to be the new secondary guild leader..<br>ehehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ugravedrifter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gravedrifter </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(3/10/02 3:08:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> additionally...</span><hr size=1> heh.. let's make it simple on them...<br><br>www.ezboard.com<br><br>go to:<br>bnitrified<br><br>Some of us are tossing around ideas of what a guild SHOULD be.<br>Also.. I am in the slow, awkward process of making a list of nearly every guild site for Quellious..